5:
So, uh, do you have any idea where
we are?
8: Um... East of the Float. I hope.
12:
Okay. Well, I hate to break it to you,
but we are in fact VERY west of the
Float.
14:
What are we going to do? We can
try to head east like the Oracle told
us, but at this rate we'll run out of
fuel soon.
19: It's okay! I'll... figure something out.
22:
HAHA! Using the incredible power
that the KING OF VOID AND
DARKNESS has granted me, I will find
us a way out of this predicament!
28: Remind me never to trust you again.
31:
All right, crew! Battle positions, NOW!
Today is the day we finally take
down that cringy role-player girl!
34: H-hey! No need to be rude...
38: You gotta admit, they aren't wrong.
42:
Aren't you supposed to be on my
side?! Besides, I'm not a role-player.
I'm the REAL DEAL. I summon
tentacles and stuff!
45:
Fair enough. But you must have
quite the reputation if even random
pirates are calling you that...
49:
I guess. But whatever, my
"reputation" got us a ship, didn't it?! 
If anything you should be thanking
me.
52:
Anyway...
PREPARE TO SINK TO THE DEPTHS of
the...A...byss?
55:
...Wait a minute. That doesn't look
good.
66:
It's just one disaster after another
today, huh...
71:
Hah! Disaster? What do you mean?
We've found the very treasure we
were looking for!
75:
A ring. All that for a ring. Does it at
least do anything?
79:
Hold on. Hmm... Yes, it's imbued with
water AND wind elements... 
Yes, that's perfect! This ring will allow 
us to breathe underwater!
84:
This is great and all, but I still don't
know the way to the abyss.
91:
Denah? What are you doing up at
this hour?
95:
Hmph! Sleep has beckoned me, and
I have refused its invitation!
...But, uh, yeah I can't seem to fall
asleep.
97:
My heart's still racing after today.
Don't you get that too, sometimes?
After a big adventure, I'm always
super restless.
106:
I guess. Today was NOTHING,
though, are you kidding me? Usually
I end up stranded on an island for at
least a month before someone finds
me.
110:
*sigh* Tell me, Denah... Why do you
do all this?
116:
I mean, let's be honest. This "King" of
yours... He doesn't exactly sound like
a good guy, does he?
118:
I'm just struggling to understand
why someone like you would want
to meet him so desperately.
122:
Hah! You wish to delve into the
depths of my SOUL? To know what
DRIVES ME? Fine, I shall regale you
with the tale
128:
Um. This is actually kind of
embarrassingI don't think I can 
get through this sober. Can we get
some booze?
131: Uh. Okay, but don't overdo it.
137:
So, long story short, I got into
roleplaying that I had dark
superpowers for a long time. And
then one day... I actually got REAL
powers.
140:
Your dreams of becoming a super
powerful dark magic user came
true, huh.
143:
Yep... But that hasn't done much to
help my reputation. People still roll
their eyes when I start talking.
150:
"Why don't you talk normally? Why
are you laughing like that? You're
not a kid anymore!"
Nobody accepts me for who I am.
154:
But I want to be someone special,
dangit! Even when I was a kid, 
I never wanted to be a boring
"normal" person. 
That's why I started making up 
these fantasies for myself.
157:
And then one day... Someone came
and turned my fantasies into reality.
160: The Lord of Darkness or whatever?
164:
The Lord of VOID AND DARKNESS! Get
it right! So, from that moment on, 
I vowed to be his eternal, loyal
subject!
168:
Even if it meant becoming a villain,
hated by the common folk!
171:
There was a long period of time
when I thought exactly that.
175: Was? You don't think that anymore?
179:
I just realized that I don't really CARE
what other people think of me
anymore! They can call me
whatever names they wantdoesn't
bother me.
186:
It's just... I want to meet him. You
know? Just once.
190:
I mean come on! What'd the
mermaid call him? The DEVOURER
OF STARS? That is SO cool.
192:
Think about it: the world exists in a
state of pure chaosuntil we
observe something for ourselves, we
can't be sure it's actually real!
194:
It's a world full of MYSTERIES out
there. Doesn't that excite you? Make
you wanna solve them all?
202:
...I can't tell, are you making fun of
me?!
205:
You're much more mature than I
initially thought.
214:
By the way, when you meet this
"Devourer of Stars", what if he
actually... you know, devours our star?
223:
Are you telling me you haven't given
it ANY thought?!
227:
I think I can handle it! Besides, you
guys will be with me too, right? We
can sort the situation out!
230:
Maybe. Since you're his servant, 
I guess we'll have to defeat you too.
That'll be a shame.
235:
H-huh?! No, no, there has to be
another way.
237:
Nope, can't think of any. Taking you
out is the only option!
